NIF or SDTM object overview

Source: R/nif_exploration.R
summary.Rd

NIF or SDTM object overview

Usage

summary(object, ...)

Arguments

object

The NIF or SDTM object.

...

Further arguments.

Value

A summary_nif or summary_sdtm object.

Examples

summary(examplinib_poc)
#> ────────SDTM data set summary ────────
#> Study 2023000022 with 80 subjects providing PC data.
#> SDTM domains: dm, vs, ex, pc, lb
#> 
#> Arms (DM):
#>   ACTARM               ACTARMCD 
#> 1 Single Arm Treatment TREATMENT
#> 2 Screen Faillure      SCRNFAIL 
#> 
#> Treatments (EX):
#>   EXTRT     
#> 1 EXAMPLINIB
#> 
#> Specimens (PC):
#> NULL
#> 
#> Analytes (PC):
#>   PCTEST     PCTESTCD  
#> 1 RS2023     RS2023    
#> 2 RS2023487A RS2023487A
#> 
#> Treatment-to-analyte mappings:
#>   EXTRT      PCTESTCD
#> 1 EXAMPLINIB RS2023  
#> 
#> Parent-to-metabolite mappings:
#>   PCTESTCD_parent PCTESTCD_metab
#> 1 RS2023          RS2023487A    
#> 
#> Time mappings:
#> none
summary(examplinib_poc_nif)
#> ──────── NONMEM input file (NIF) object summary ────────
#> Data from 80 subjects across one study:
#>  STUDYID      N    
#>  2023000022   80

#>

#>  moderate   20   
#>  normal     8    
#> 
#> Administered drugs:
#>  RS2023
#> 
#> Analytes:
#>  RS2023, RS2023487A
#> 
#> Subjects per dose levels:
#>  RS2023   N    
#>  500      80   
#> 
#> 1344 observations:
#>  CMT   ANALYTE      N     
#>  2     RS2023       672   
#>  3     RS2023487A   672

#>

#>  PARENT   min   max   mean   median   
#>  RS2023   14    98    65.4   67
